addAllData(String[], byte[][]) - Method in interface net.mtrop.doom.Wad
Deprecated.
2.7.0 - The reason why this method was added in the first place was to have a bulk add operation that incurred hopefully less transaction overhead in implementations. WadMap, of course, cannot add data. In WadBuffer, the performance overhead was already moot, and WadFile has WadFile.createAdder() for large add operations to reduce the overhead.

Deprecated.
2.7.0 - The reason why this method was added in the first place was to have a bulk add operation that incurred hopefully less transaction overhead in implementations. In WadBuffer, the performance overhead was already moot, and WadFile has methods that delay the writing of the entry list, which, although less "safe," solves this problem by allowing the user to defer the final write via WadFile.flushEntries().
